	     Maputo - Two policemen have been killed in a string of attacks on police stations in a small town in northern Mozambique but 14 of the gunmen were slain, police said on Saturday. "We recorded 14 deaths and several wounded among the bandits," police spokesperson Inacio Dina told AFP of the attacks in Mocimboa de Praia. Two policemen were also killed during what appeared to be coordinated attacks that occurred on Thursday and Friday. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  